-- Chesapeake Energy sells shale to BHP unit for $4.75 billion
-- 
-- Mon Feb 21, 2011 6:00pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2011/02/21/us-chesapeake-idUSTRE71K6A020110221

 

 BANGALORE  (Reuters) - Chesapeake Energy Corp ( CHK.N ) said it is selling its holdings in Arkansas' Fayetteville shale natural gas field to a unit of BHP Billiton ( BHP.AX ) ( BLT.L ) for $4.75 billion in cash. 

 Chesapeake said the deal with BHP Billiton Petroleum includes existing net production of about 415 million cubic feet of natural gas equivalent per day and midstream assets with about 420 miles of pipeline. Chesapeake has agreed to provide essential services for up to one year for BHP Billiton's Fayetteville properties. The deal is expected to close in the first half of 2011. (Reporting by  Saqib Iqbal Ahmed  in Bangalore; Editing by Maju Samuel)